titleInfo.title: Primerica Life Insurance Company v. Cassie et al
titleInfo.subTitle: STIPULATION and ORDER signed by Senior Judge William B. Shubb on 11/30/2012 DISCHARGING Primerica and its agents, attorneys, and assigns of all liability with respect to life insurance policy number 0430744571; DISMISSING, with prejudice, Primerica and its agents, attorneys and assigns as to all claims relating to said policy; ENJOINING and RESTRAINING all Defendants-in-Interpleader and their agents, attorneys and assigns from instituting any suit at law or equity, or action of any kind against Primerica and its agents, attorneys and assigns, with respect to the policy; AWARDING Primerica $6,556.00 for reasonable attorneys' fees and costs; DISTRIBUTING policy proceeds to Primerica Life Insurance Company for the amount of $6,556.00; to P.L. Fry for the amount of $11,218.62; to Patrick Williams for the amount of $209,197.98. (Michel, G) Modified on 12/3/2012 (Michel, G).

titleInfo.title: Primerica Life Insurance Company v. Cassie et al
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER signed by Senior Judge William B. Shubb on 3/20/13. Before ruling on 54 Petition for Court Approval, the court requires additional documentation regarding the attorney's fees to be distributed pursuant to the Settlement and Release Agreement to Primerica's counsel, Felicia Morrison, and Neumiller&Beardslee. Documentation of the kind listed in Eastern District Local Rule 293(c) would be of assistance to the court. Alternatively, should Primerica's counsel, Felicia Morrison, and Neumiller&Beardslee agree to each reduce their fees by one-third, the court would require no additional information. To allow for a response to the court's request, the hearing on this matter is hereby CONTINUED until 4/22/13 at 2:00 p.m. Within 14 days of this Order, counsel for Shandria Bogle and Ryan Martin, Felicia Morrison, shall either file the requested information or notify the court that all counsel agree to reduce their fees by one-third. (Meuleman, A) Modified on 4/2/2013 (Kirksey Smith, K).
